We may blockade an enemy-controlled system by simply moving one of our fleets to a system where no enemy fleet is located.  Blockading a Rebel-controlled system will prevent the Rebel Alliance from accessing crucial resources. While the blockade remains, production stops, mines and refineries produce no materials, and all maintenance from them is lost; in addition, any personnel or troops located at that system prior to the blockade risk capture or destruction should they attempt to escape the blockade.  Of course, the population of a system will resent our blockading force, and loyalty may eventually swing against us.